title: Neptis mixophyes
text:
Neptis mixophyes, or Holland's clubbed sailer, is a <a href="butterfly">butterfly</a> in the family <a href="Nymphalidae">Nymphalidae</a>. It is found in eastern <a href="Sierra%20Leone">Sierra Leone</a>, <a href="Ivory%20Coast">Ivory Coast</a>, <a href="Ghana">Ghana</a>, <a href="Nigeria">Nigeria</a>, <a href="Cameroon">Cameroon</a>, <a href="Gabon">Gabon</a>, the <a href="Republic%20of%20the%20Congo">Republic of the Congo</a>, <a href="Equatorial%20Guinea">Equatorial Guinea</a> and the <a href="Democratic%20Republic%20of%20the%20Congo">Democratic Republic of the Congo</a>. The habitat consists of wetter forests.
The larvae feed on "<a href="Dalhousiea%20africana">Dalhousiea africana</a>" and "<a href="Petersianthus">Petersianthus</a>" species.
